<h1>11/27 planning meeting minutes</h1>

<P><B>Next meeting: 12/12 or 12/13 to review individual lecture plans</B></P>

<h2>Structure</h2>

<ul>
  <li> Communications infrastructures history (4) - Randy
  <li> Computing history (4) - Armando
  <li> Democratization &amp; societal effects (4) - Steve
  <li> Convergence and future (3) - all?
</ul>

<h2>Logistics</h2>

<p>
Write presentations at 45-minute granularity.  Present in "interleaved"
form throughout semester.  "Weekly features" (around which lectures are
structured) include:
</p>

<ul>
  <li> Inventor or entrepreneur of the week (background; their effect or
       role; where are they now)
  <li> Armando: "computer containment structure of the week" to
       illustrate shrinkage.  Whole lab, single room, big truck, big
       car, desktop, backpack, pocket.
  <li> Show &amp; tell artifact of the week
  <li> Dilbert of the week
  <li> WWW "directed scavenger hunts" for students to look up additional
       info on some topic related to lectures
</ul>

<h2>Student activities</h2>

<ul>
  <li> Out-of-band field trip ideas: Marconi Center (Randy), "Computer
       Museum West",
       Intel museum (Armando)
  <li> <a href="reading.html">Readings</a>
  <li> Maybe poster session for student projects (like Dave Patterson
       does for 252)?
</ul>

